2 (1). Pronotum in dorsal view, with anterior half of lateral carinae converging anteriorly; not explanate laterally, surface convexly curved to lateral carinae; lateral carinae in lateral view distinctly thicker anteriorly, anterior thickness 2× posterior thickness (
Fig. 3D
); pronotal disc lacking longitudinal groove extending anteriorly from lateral basal pore in margin (
Fig. 3B
); metatibia triangularly dilated toward apex (
Fig. 3F
)............................................ [subgenus 

Ceratophila

] … 
3

- Pronotum, in dorsal view, with central 2/3 of lateral carinae nearly parallel (
Figs. 4A
, 
5A
), explanate laterally, surface broadly concave near lateral carinae; lateral carina weakly thickening anteriorly, anterior thickness <1.5× that at base (
Fig. 3E
); pronotal disc with longitudinal groove extending anteriorly from lateral basal pore in margin (
Fig. 3A
); metatibia not triangularly dilated toward apex (
Fig. 3G
)............................. [subgenus 


Vovidesa
Tang, Skelley & Pérez-Farrera


